name: Diana Taurasi
summary: Diana Taurasi has etched her name in history by winning an unprecedented sixth Olympic gold medal, becoming the most decorated Olympian in basketball history. Her unwavering pursuit of victory, despite being 39 years old and facing Father Time, has been remarkable. Despite losing her starting spot to the younger Jackie Young, Taurasi has remained vital to Team USA's success. Her unparalleled basketball prowess, leadership, and ability to deliver in crucial moments has been instrumental in the team's dominance. This latest achievement adds to her already illustrious career and serves as a testament to her remarkable longevity and determination to leave an enduring legacy in the sport.

name: Brittney Griner
summary: In a powerful display of resilience, Brittney Griner shed tears of joy and gratitude during the US women's basketball team's gold medal ceremony at the Paris Olympics. Griner's emotional reaction was a testament to her perseverance after enduring a harrowing 10-month imprisonment in Russia. The victory held profound significance for her, as it represented a triumph over adversity and a return to the Olympic stage. Griner's unwavering spirit and emotional outburst resonated deeply with the public, capturing her profound appreciation for the moment and the journey that led her there.

name: Winter Olympics 2026
summary: The 2026 Winter Olympics will be held in Milan and Cortina d'Ampezzo, Italy, from February 6 to 22, 2026. The 2028 Summer Olympics will be held in Los Angeles, California, USA, from July 14 to 30, 2028. The International Olympic Committee (IOC) awarded the hosting rights to these cities in 2019 and 2017, respectively. The 2026 Winter Olympics will be the first time that two cities have jointly hosted the Winter Games since 1924, when Chamonix, France, and St. Moritz, Switzerland, shared hosting duties. The 2026 Winter Olympics will feature 95 events across 15 disciplines, including new events in women's ski jumping and mixed team ski jumping.
